<a href="http://www.sportngin.com">Sport Ngin</a> is looking for a passionate Front-End Software Engineer to work on a new and ambitious client-side JavaScript application.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">The successful candidate will thrive in an open, relaxed, creative atmosphere - with a team of extremely talented developers and designers in a fantastic NE Minneapolis loft-style office space (13 foot ceilings, hardwood floors, brick and timber finish, and tons of windows). We hook our development staff up with MacBook Pros, big ol&#39; flat panels, and all the software they need to create amazing work. We offer competitive pay and great benefits.</span></p>
<p>
<a href="http://sportngin.com">Sport Ngin</a>, an established and successful business since 2002 and recently voted 1 of Minnesota&#39;s Top 100 Companies to work for, brings web-based SaaS offerings to the sports world.</p>
<p>
<strong>As a member of the Development team at Sport Ngin, you&#39;ll.......</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Build a new client-side Node.js application from the ground up for mobile, tablet and desktop.</li>
<li>
Use both Node.js and JavaScript MVC frameworks to communciate with an existing Ruby on Rails application via a JSON API.</li>
<li>
Work with the talented Ruby Developers and Designers behind the Sport Ngin platform.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>This is the perfect role for you if you.....</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Are a passionate JavaScript developer with familiarity using Node.js.</li>
<li>
Have experience using JavaScript libraries such as jQuery, YUI, MooTools, Prototype.</li>
<li>
Are familiar with JavaScript MVC frameworks such as SproutCore, JavaScriptMVC, Backbone.js.</li>
<li>
Have knowledge and experience with other programming languages such as Ruby, Python, Java, PHP.</li>
<li>
Are comfortable with version control such as Git, Mercurial or Subversion.</li>
<li>
Have mobile development experience.</li>
<li>
Have familiarity with agile development techniques including test-driven development and priority-based planning</li>
<li>
Possess solid object-oriented design skills, knowledge of software patterns, and experience modeling data-driven applications.</li>
<li>
Have an ability to communicate and collaborate effectively with designers and other developers.</li>
<li>
Have an independent and self-motivated nature with the ability to work alone, on a team and/or leading a team of developers.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Preferably you have strong experience and knowledge with the following.....</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Languages and Systems: JavaScript (Node.js),&nbsp;Ruby (on Rails), Python, Java, PHP, SQL</li>
<li>
Web Services: REST, SOAP, APIs</li>
<li>
Data Formats: HTML, XML, JSON, HTTP, CSS</li>
</ul>
